comments.body: @eliotjordan I'm sorry to come back to this--it looks like I need to reverse myself. We need to *display* the external name in pulfalight, but we need to *pass to Aeon* the internal name (i.e. the code) for requesting. It looks like right now, what's getting passed to Aeon is the external name. Could you fix that? Thanks, and sorry again!

@eliotjordan Are you sure? Those codes are the ones which Aeon uses to decide which queue to put things into - I think the only valid values are `RBSC`, `MUDD`, and `Engineering Library` (and I'm not 100% sure Engineering Library is right either.)

There's also `location_codes.yml` and `storage_notes.yml` which might be where we want the longer form names?

I see now that the UI text for the locations goes here:
https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/blob/main/config/location_codes.yml

Not sure about the physloc codes. Maybe something like:

```
scamudd: 'scamudd'
```

if those codes are what Aeon is expecting.

So does pulfalight map the Aeon "sites", i.e. pickup locations? If so, they are:
| site | physloc | Alma label
| --- | --- | ---
RBSC | scarcpxm | 'Manuscripts Remote Storage (ReCAP). Special Collections Use Only'
RBSC | scactsn | 'Cotsen Children’s Library Archival. Special Collections Use Only'
RBSC | scagax | 'Graphic Arts Archival. Special Collections Use Only'
RBSC | scamss | 'Manuscripts Archival. Special Collections Use Only'
RBSC | scawa | 'Western Americana Archival. Special Collections Use Only'
RBSC | scaex | 'Rare Books Archival. Special Collections Use Only'
RBSC | scahsvm | 'Manuscripts High Security Archival. Special Collections Use Only'
MUDD | scamudd | 'Mudd Archival. Special Collections Use Only'
RBSC | scathx | 'Theater Archival. Special Collections Use Only'

Ah, okay. Pulfalight does two things:

Map `physloc` to SITE:

https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/blob/2d88ebe0e49d76515a0910d4db79c265de18b06e/app/values/aeon_request.rb#L85-L87

and

https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/blob/2d88ebe0e49d76515a0910d4db79c265de18b06e/lib/pulfalight/traject/ead2_config.rb#L99-L106

and also map container locations to Location

https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/blob/2d88ebe0e49d76515a0910d4db79c265de18b06e/app/values/aeon_request.rb#L98-L100

and 

https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/blob/2d88ebe0e49d76515a0910d4db79c265de18b06e/app/values/aeon_request.rb#L109-L112

I think you need some tests in https://github.com/pulibrary/pulfalight/blob/main/spec/values/aeon_request_spec.rb to

A) Make sure Site gets populated for those physloc codes
B) Make sure Location replaces those sca codes with the other codes.

The goal is, in Aeon, for `scahsvm` to have a `Location` of `hsvm` and a `Site` of `RBSC`, for instance, yeah?
Alternatively, if we want the UI and Aeon to always act as if "sca" isn't in a location code, we could just index without those - if it finds "scaxxx" it indexes "xxx"

Oh, that is so much better! Yes, that would be ideal. The raison d'etre of the new codes is purely to allow us to have things in the catalog BUT not have them requestable from there; they are "twins" to existing location codes in each case. So indexing with out the `sca`- prefix sounds like an elegant solution. That way bibdata indexes with the prefix and facilitates disallowing requesting; pulfalight indexes without prefix and sends to Aeon as usual.
